\begin_layout Standard
Factor utilization is added to the model to help generate pro-cyclical value
 added per worker.
 In order to counter diminishing returns across all factors of production
 due to capital rigidity, it is necessary to compensate with a mechanism
 that increases total factor productivity.
 The equations used are flexible adaptations of the following idea.
 Let the firm have gross output given by a function of the type 
\begin_inset Formula $Q_{t}=Q\left(u_{t}X_{t}\right)$
\end_inset

 with a generic first-order condition for optimal choice of 
\begin_inset Formula $X_{t}$
\end_inset

 given by 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
P_{t}\frac{\partial Q_{t}}{\partial\left(u_{t}X_{t}\right)}u_{t}=P_{t}^{X}
\]

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $P_{t}^{X}$
\end_inset

 is the user cost of 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

.
 Utilization is then associated with an auxiliary stock variable 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

 which obeys the following law of motion 
\begin_inset Formula $x_{t}=\left(u_{t}-1\right)X_{t}+\lambda_{t}x_{t-1}$
\end_inset

 where 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda_{t}=\bar{u}_{t-1}^{1/\eta}/\beta_{t}$
\end_inset

, and where 
\begin_inset Formula $\bar{u}_{t}$
\end_inset

